<subSubSection id="C3590FD3154BE81501858C91B227FBDD" pageId="1" pageNumber="377" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BFC5C58154BE81501858C91B227FBDD" blockId="1.[151,1436,963,1134]" pageId="1" pageNumber="377">
<emphasis id="B937804A154BE81501858C91B648FC49" bold="true" box="[151,266,963,989]" pageId="1" pageNumber="377">Diagnosis</emphasis>
. The subgenus is described in details by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFD221A9154BE81503CC8C91B4C9FC49" author="Karisch, T." box="[734,907,963,989]" pageId="1" pageNumber="377" pagination="39 - 197" refId="ref3896" refString="Karisch, T. (2013) Taxonomic revision of the African Cyana - species (Lepidoptera: Arctiidae, Lithosiinae) (pls. 15 - 19). Esperiana, 18, 39 - 197." type="journal article" year="2013">Karisch (2013)</bibRefCitation>
. Except the characteristic external appearance, the subgenus is characterized by the scobinated anellus, large aedeagus and vesica bearing two clusters of numerous robust spines in male genitalia, and thick-walled and rugose corpus bursae and the appendix bursae consisting of a thick-walled and rugose, tube-like basal section and a membranous globular distal section in female genitalia.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3590FD3154BE81501D58B01B4C8FBF9" box="[199,906,1107,1134]" pageId="1" pageNumber="377" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="8BFC5C58154BE81501D58B01B4C8FBF9" blockId="1.[151,1436,963,1134]" box="[199,906,1107,1134]" pageId="1" pageNumber="377">
<emphasis id="B937804A154BE81501D58B01B61BFBF9" bold="true" box="[199,345,1107,1133]" pageId="1" pageNumber="377">Distribution</emphasis>
. The subgenus is endemic for 
<collectingCountry id="F3541CC8154BE81503A28B01B4C4FBF9" box="[688,902,1107,1133]" name="Madagascar Island" pageId="1" pageNumber="377">Madagascar Island</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
